Description: The USS Hornet consists of eight ships of the United States Navy that served in several wars and missions.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The USS Hornet consists of eight ships of the United States Navy, including USS Hornet (1775), USS Hornet (1805 sloop), USS Hornet (1805 brig), USS Hornet (1813), USS Hornet (1865), USS Hornet (1898), USS Hornet (CV-8), and USS Hornet (CV-12). The USS Hornet (1775) was a ten-gun sloop commissioned in 1775 and served in the American Revolutionary War. USS Hornet (1805 sloop) was also a ten-gun sloop and took part in the First Barbary War. USS Hornet (1805 brig) was a brig-rigged sloop of war launched on July 28, 1805, and sank in a storm on September 29, 1829. USS Hornet (1813) was a five-gun schooner used as a dispatch vessel between 1814 and 1820. USS Hornet (1865), the first to be steam propelled, was an iron, side-wheeled steamer. USS Hornet (1898), a converted yacht, was a dispatch vessel in the Spanish–American War. USS Hornet (CV-8), launched the Doolittle Raid in 1942, fought at the Battle of Midway, and was sunk at the Battle of the Santa Cruz Islands on October 26, 1942. USS Hornet (CV-12) was originally named Kearsarge, but renamed in honor of CV-8 and active through the rest of World War II and is preserved as a museum ship in Alameda, California.

Description: Miguel Delgado, M.D., is a San Francisco Bay Area cosmetic and plastic surgeon in the United States
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Miguel Delgado, M.D., is a San Francisco Bay Area cosmetic and plastic surgeon who holds the two credentials most coveted by plastic surgeons practicing in the United States, namely certification by the American Board of Plastic Surgery and membership in the American Society of Plastic Surgery. Dr. Delgado has been in practice since 1990 and specializes in elective cosmetic surgery. He has two office locations: one at 450 Sutter Street in San Francisco and the other in Marin County at 165 Rowland Way in Novato. Dr. Delgado was privileged to train at some of the most prestigious institutions in the country. He graduated with honors from medical school at the University of California San Francisco in 1982 and continued with his internship and residency at Johns Hopkins University teaching hospital in Baltimore, Maryland. He completed a plastic surgery residency at Stony Brook University Medical Center in East Meadow, New York.Dr. Delgado has extensive training in the following surgical procedure with the added benefit of 30 years of experience.His expertise is in facelift surgery, mommy makeover, tummy tucks, breast implant revision surgery like En-Bloc breast implant removal, all types of breast surgery, all types of body contouring especially after massive weight loss including arm lifts (Brachioplasty), and thigh lifts. In addition, Dr. Delgado has become a world authority in gynecomastia (male breast enlargement or man boobs) and the treatment with male breast reduction surgery. Miguel Delgado, M.D., and his team take great pride when patients are happy and confident in their results. He has generated an impressive number of online reviews with over 985 reviews with an average rating of 4.8. Ninety-five percent of these reviews are patients who have completed surgery. He was voted “Best Plastic Surgeon in the San Francisco Bay Area” by the San Francisco Magazine for both 2020 and 2021. He has been honored by a variety of National Top doctor organizations, including Castle Connolly Top Doctors for his excellent surgical skills and his commitment to high-quality patient care. His work and practice have been seen on the BBC, Discovery Channel, NBC, and various radio and media outlets throughout the world.

Description: ACM is a consortium of 14 liberal arts colleges, offers off-campus study and professional development opportunities.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Associated Colleges of the Midwest has offered consortial off-campus study programs for more than 40 years. Individual ACM colleges also offer programs in locations around the world and in subjects ranging from art history to marine biology. Each year, nearly 1,500 students from ACM colleges spend a term or longer on an off-campus study program. On some ACM campuses, one-half to three-fourths of recent graduating classes have participated in off-campus study. ACM colleges have a rich history of shared commitment to promoting excellence in teaching and learning, especially as achieved through collaboration.
